parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, leading to a loss of vehicle control, increased risk of accidents, and potential fires.
The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the cooling fan clutch assembly can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage and potential fires.
The failure of the brake system can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose vital information about the vehicle's operation, increasing the risk of accidents.
Transmission fluid leakage onto the catalytic converter can cause damage to the engine and potentially lead to a fire.
symptoms: unusual noises or smells from the transmission.
